UPSTREAM STATUS: FULLY MERGED — do not apply to any 6.x kernel.

The ROG Flow X13 (GV301) tablet mode support was merged upstream across
several commits between 6.1 and 6.5:

  - asus-wmi.h: asus_wmi_lid_flip_rog_devid added to tablet_switch_mode enum
  - asus-nb-wmi.c: GV301 DMI match with quirk_asus_tablet_mode
  - asus-nb-wmi.c: 0xBD keymap entry for ROG xflow lid flip
  - amd-sfh-hid: KBGUARD sensor support merged separately

The original patch (arglebargle-arch, targeting 5.16.x) is no longer needed.
This file is kept for historical reference only.

To verify on a running 6.x kernel:
  grep -r "GV301" /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/build/drivers/platform/x86/ 2>/dev/null
  # or check: /sys/bus/platform/drivers/asus-nb-wmi/
